Seeing, then, that the text of the Decem Scriptores is capable of considerable amendment, and is unaccompanied by such explanatory notes and elucidations as historica] readers are accustomed to meet with, the Council of the Surtees Society resolved to place the Worlcs of Symeon of Durham on their list of intended publicatione.
